{"id":441365,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmanuel_Kriaras","text":"Emmanuel G. Kriaras (; 28 November 1906 \u2013 22 August 2014) was a Greek lexicographer and philologist. He was Emeritus Professor of the School of Philosophy at the Aristotle University of Thessaloniki. He was a student of Ioannis Psycharis. He practiced the ideology of demotic Greek and his work was mainly on all the language matters of Greek and Greece.\nKriaras was born in Piraeus, Attica.\nKriaras died in Thessaloniki, Greece from a heart attack. He was 107 years old.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Greeks","surface_form":"Greek","offset":64},{"uri":"Lexicography","surface_form":"lexicographer","offset":70},{"uri":"Philology","surface_form":"philologist","offset":88},{"uri":"Professor_Emeritus","surface_form":"Emeritus Professor","offset":108},{"uri":"Philosophy","surface_form":"Philosophy","offset":144},{"uri":"Aristotle_University_of_Thessaloniki","surface_form":"Aristotle University of Thessaloniki","offset":162},{"uri":"Student","surface_form":"student","offset":209},{"uri":"Ioannis_Psycharis","surface_form":"Ioannis Psycharis","offset":220},{"uri":"Ideology","surface_form":"ideology","offset":256},{"uri":"Greek_language","surface_form":"demotic Greek","offset":268},{"uri":"Greece","surface_form":"Greece","offset":347},{"uri":"Piraeus","surface_form":"Piraeus","offset":375},{"uri":"Attica","surface_form":"Attica","offset":384},{"uri":"Thessaloniki","surface_form":"Thessaloniki","offset":408},{"uri":"Heart_attack","surface_form":"heart attack","offset":436}]}